Oct 9 2006 	Great Hotel off the Strip	My husband and I went to the Mardi Gras in Las Vegas it was all we could afford as we did a multi destination trip and we were renewing our wedding vowes there.On arrival we found the staff to be very pleasent they helped us with our luggage and made sure we were comfortable in our room.We chose this hotel as it has accessible rooms (my husband is in a wheelchair). As disabled rooms go we found this to be about 85% accessible just a little problem with the toilet which we got around between us.The downside is that the shuttle bus is not wheelchair accessible which ment the only way to the strip was either to walk it (if you are fit enough) or if you get the monorail which is fine but quite expensive over 5 days we spent approx $105 on monorail fares or of course taxis if you are really rich, the buses are accessible but again you need to get the monorail to get the bus to freemont st.The view may not have been fantastic but for a base it was good, we felt quite safe walking back from the monorail centre even at 1.30am, we asked about the area at the monorail centre who said that it was next to a 5* hotel so the area is perfectly safe. We had no problem at all.The restaurant and meals we found to be very resonable for the evening, we didn't bother with breakfast we just went to the 7 eleven up the road the night before to pick up milk and cereal which we were able to put in the room fridge.Overall we found no fault with this hotel apart from not being able to use the complimentary shuttle bus which put added expense on our trip.We would go there again.	
Oct 6 2006 	On a budget? This is the place to go.	Me and a friend stayed at the Best Western on Paradise in May for 7 nights, and as far as a base is concerned, this was perfect. 2 minutes away from the main strip, 100m from the mono-rail, which drops u off at about 6 different hotels if you didnt want to pay for taxis. The staff were friendly, especially the 2 bar maids. Check in was a bit of a slow process due to there being only 2 receptionists but we got there in the end. The rooms were very large with a good amount of storage space. The bathroom was tiny, and when your'e 6'1, you need all the space u can get. I ended up getting dried in the main room due to the vast amount of space there was. The views are ok if u get an internal room. That faces the pool and gardens, if your not so lucky, as we were, you get an outside facing room and i can tell you that you wouldn't want to really be walking round that area late at night. It's a bit seedy ! The food was very good and i can recommend the T-Bone steak and everything was reasonably priced. Overall, if u want somewhere that's cheap and to lay your head and get freshened up, this'll be fine. If your after luxury, get a hotel on the strip.	
