Jun 3 2006 	Clean Good Food and Cheap Beer!!	My company booked this hotel for a convention in May 2006. Let's just say it's average. It is better than some and not as good as others. I had room 3145 which is a king poolside on the 3rd floor. The room was very clean with a loveseat,chair, end table, and coffee table, and there was a nook with a sink, dorm sized refrigerator, a sink, and a 4 cup coffeemaker. The food in the restaurant is very good and very reasonable, but service is a little slow at times. A huge club sandwich is $7.95 and is larger than most typical restaurants. The beer is cheap compaired to everywhere else in Las Vegas. A large draft is $3.00 there is a happy hour every night from 4pm-6pm and some nights it was from 12am-6am as well. The bar is open 24/7 and the restaurant is open from 6am-midnight. The shuttle takes you to Bally's (Near Caesars Palace/Paris) and to the airport. This is every hour on the hour until 11pm. Take advantage of the shuttle to Bally's as this will save you at least one way of cab fare to/from the strip. They will also pick you up at Bally's if you call and let them know. It is also only about 300 yards from the Las Vegas Convention Center and the Las Vegas Monorail station at the Convention Center. I'll reiterate what other reviews have said as well. It's definately not a 4 star property, but overall it's safe, clean, and not to out of the way. Visit their website directly at: [-] where they have web only specials that other sites can't beat and that includes [-].	
